llution, contaminated food supply, recreational drug use, HIV/AIDS, cancer, chronic conditions (allergies, diabetes, obesity, arthritis), famine, natural disasters, and war. May be taken for credit two times when topics vary.' ),( 'LTCS 165' , 'Special Topics: The Politics of Food', 'This course will examine the representation and politics of
